  <div id="hdb" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <DefBox
      term="Keeping a Bichon Frise in an HDB flat"
      definition="The Bichon Frise is named on the HDB-approved breed list, so you can keep one in an HDB flat. HDB allows one dog of an approved breed per flat, and the Bichon's compact 3 to 5 kg size sits comfortably within the small-breed rules. Every Bichon Frise we place has its dog licensing completed at purchase, so the paperwork is handled for you."
      bridge="Is a Bichon Frise HDB-approved? Yes, by name on the list, and it has been a Singapore flat favourite for decades. Just mind the one-dog-per-flat rule, and if you already have a dog, message us first so we can check your situation."
      citationLabel="Read HDB's guidelines on keeping pets"
